The global remote pregnancy monitoring market is segmented based on product type, connectivity, end-user, and region. In terms of product type, the market is divided into wearable devices, stationary devices, and pregnancy tracking kits. Wearable devices are gaining popularity due to their convenience and continuous monitoring capabilities. The connectivity segment includes Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, and other forms of connectivity. Hospitals, specialty clinics, and homecare settings are the primary end-users of remote pregnancy monitoring solutions. Geographically, the market is analyzed across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East and Africa.

